            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>15-45 minutes is the effective range for most platforms. Under 10 minutes doesn't give the platform algorithm time to distribute the stream. TikTok Live sessions running 30+ minutes receive more algorithmic push than shorter sessions. For Facebook and Instagram, 20-40 minutes consistently outperforms both shorter and longer durations for engagement rate.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Do you need professional equipment for live video?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>No. A smartphone with a stable internet connection (minimum 5 Mbps upload speed), a ring light or window lighting, and a $20-30 clip-on microphone produces professional-quality results. Poor audio drives more viewer dropoff than poor video quality. Invest in audio first, then lighting, then video stabilization.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
