            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Choose based on your existing audience: Instagram Live for visual brands with an 18-35 demographic, TikTok Live for discovery and younger audiences, LinkedIn Live for B2B and professional audiences, YouTube Live for evergreen long-form content that benefits from search indexing, Facebook Live for community-first brands with older demographics.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How does live video compare to pre-recorded video for engagement?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Facebook reports live videos receive 6x more engagement than regular videos. The engagement advantage comes from three factors: platform push notifications to followers, algorithmic prioritization of live content in feeds, and the real-time interaction element that keeps viewers engaged longer than passive video consumption.</p></div></div>
          </div>
